    "Its testing set accuracy of 97.2% is higher than that of competing models, and it offers a unique approach to identifying and categorizing potato leaf diseases.",
    "In another study (Al-Amin et al, 2019), researchers used a DCNN to identify late and early blight in potato harvests.",
    "Their research aimed to identify diseased potato leaves from healthy ones so that the infections may be detected early.",
    "To train and test the model, 2250 image samples of potato leaves were used.",
    "The DCNN was developed using a custom-built architecture for identifying diseased potato leaves."
